editorialSummary.text: Creative, oat-milk & plant-based ice creams dished up in a compact, contemporary parlor.

originalText.text:
Urban Dessert Lab presents a refreshing twist on traditional ice cream, offering a haven for the plant-based community and dessert lovers alike. The space, though cozy with seating for just a few, creates an intimate ambiance, perfect for savoring their unique creations.

The all-plant-based menu is a delightful nod to sustainability and health-conscious indulgence. While the space might be compact, the flavors are anything but. The ice cream, a pleasant surprise in every scoop, provides a delightful option for those strolling through the neighborhood.

In essence, Urban Dessert Lab isn‚Äôt just about ice cream; it‚Äôs about experiencing innovation and inclusivity in every bite. It‚Äôs a small but mighty testament to how plant-based options can be both delectable and environmentally friendly, making it a must-visit spot for anyone looking to satisfy their sweet tooth with a conscience.

originalText.text: Urban Dessert Lab in New York is a sweet haven that deserves high praise. The innovative dessert creations showcase a perfect blend of flavors, textures, and artistic presentation. From the mouthwatering ice cream sandwiches to the delectable mochi donuts, each treat is a culinary masterpiece. The use of high-quality, unique ingredients sets Urban Dessert Lab apart, catering to both classic and adventurous palates. The modern and cozy ambiance adds to the overall delightful experience, making it a must-visit for dessert enthusiasts. The friendly staff and commitment to excellence make this dessert destination a standout in the vibrant New York culinary scene.

absolutely incredible!!! can't believe i've been sleeping on this gem. had the strawberry shortcake and it tasted unbelievable. really affordable and the service was superb.

EVERYTHING PlANT BASED! need i say more?

the only downside was very limited seating and space inside. feels a bit claustrophobic but damn the desserts were 100% worth it.
